        <dt>Identification and Creation</dt>
        <dd>
          <dl>
            <dt>Object Number</dt>
            <dd>1943.840</dd>

                            <dt>People</dt>
                <dd>
                                                                 <a href=https://www.harvardartmuseums.org/collections/person/26693>Jean-Auguste-Dominique Ingres</a>, French                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          (Montauban 1780 - 1867 Paris)
                                            <br>
                                    </dd>
            
                            <dt>Title</dt>
                <dd>Portrait of Augustin Jordan and his Daughter Adrienne</dd>
            
                                                                                                            
                            <dt>Classification</dt>
                <dd>Drawings</dd>
                                        <dt>Work Type</dt>
                <dd>
                                                            drawing                                                      </dd>
                                        <dt>Date</dt>
                <dd>1817</dd>
                                                                <dt>Culture</dt>
                <dd>French</dd>
                            <dt>Persistent Link</dt>
                <dd><a href="https://hvrd.art/o/297940">https://hvrd.art/o/297940</a></dd>
          </dl>
        </dd>

        
                <dt>Physical Descriptions</dt>
        <dd>
          <dl>
                          <dt>Medium</dt>
              <dd>Graphite on white wove paper</dd>
            
           
           
                          <dt>Dimensions</dt>
              <dd>43 x 32.3 cm (16 15/16 x 12 11/16 in.)<br />
frame: 70.2 x 55.8 cm (27 5/8 x 21 15/16 in.)</dd>
            
            
            
            
            
            
          </dl>
        </dd>
        
                  <dt>Provenance</dt>
          <dd>Augustin Jordan, Lyon; his daughter baronne Octave Despatys de Courteilles; her son Pierre-Camille-Augustin-Omer Despatys; his son Pierre-Jérôme Despatys; Wildenstein and Co., Paris, 1922, acquired from them by Grenville L. Winthrop, March 1923 (Fr 140,000 for both); his bequest to the Fogg Art Museum, 1943.</dd>
        
        
        
        <dt>Acquisition and Rights</dt>
        <dd>
          <dl>
                          <dt>Credit Line</dt>
              <dd>Harvard Art Museums/Fogg Museum, Bequest of Grenville L. Winthrop</dd>
            
            
                          <dt>Accession Year</dt>
              <dd>1943</dd>
            
            <dt>Object Number</dt>
            <dd>1943.840</dd>

                          <dt>Division</dt>
              <dd>European and American Art</dd>
            
                          <dt>Contact</dt>
              <dd><a href="mailto:am_europeanamerican@harvard.edu"><span>am_europeanamerican@harvard.edu</span></a></dd>
